import os
import hashlib
from collections import defaultdict

DATA_DIR = r''D:\\SLIIT\\Reaserch Project\\CoconutHealthMonitor\\Research\\ml\\data\\raw\\pest_mite\\dataset_v2''

def get_file_hash\(filepath\):
    with open\(filepath, ''rb''\) as f:
        return hashlib.md5\(f.read\(\)\).hexdigest\(\)

# Collect all image hashes
print\(''Checking for DUPLICATE IMAGES between train/val/test...''\)
print\(''='' * 60\)

all_hashes = defaultdict\(list\)
splits = [''train'', ''validation'', ''test'']
classes = [''coconut_mite'', ''healthy'']

for split in splits:
    for cls in classes:
        folder = os.path.join\(DATA_DIR, split, cls\)
        if os.path.exists\(folder\):
            for f in os.listdir\(folder\):
                if f.lower\(\).endswith\(\(''.jpg'', ''.jpeg'', ''.png''\)\):
                    filepath = os.path.join\(folder, f\)
                    h = get_file_hash\(filepath\)
                    all_hashes[h].append\(f''{split}/{cls}/{f}''\)

# Find duplicates
duplicates = {h: paths for h, paths in all_hashes.items\(\) if len\(paths\) > 1}

print\(f''Total unique images: {len\(all_hashes\)}''\)
print\(f''Duplicate image groups: {len\(duplicates\)}''\)

if duplicates:
    print\(\)
    print\(''DUPLICATES FOUND:''\)
    print\(''-'' * 60\)
    count = 0
    for h, paths in list\(duplicates.items\(\)\)[:10]:  # Show first 10
        count += 1
        print\(f''\\nDuplicate #{count}:''\)
        for p in paths:
            print\(f''  - {p}''\)
    if len\(duplicates\) > 10:
        print\(f''\\n... and {len\(duplicates\) - 10} more duplicate groups''\)
        
    # Count cross-split duplicates
    cross_split = 0
    for h, paths in duplicates.items\(\):
        splits_in_group = set\(p.split\(''/''\)[0] for p in paths\)
        if len\(splits_in_group\) > 1:
            cross_split += 1
    print\(f''\\nCROSS-SPLIT DUPLICATES \(train-test leak\): {cross_split}''\)
else:
    print\(''No duplicates found.''\)
")
